This paper deals with the problem of radio resource management in heterogeneous networks (HetNets) with flexible backhaul. The paper focuses on optimizing flow control, routing, interference mitigation, and link scheduling to maximize network utility. This problem is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, given the focus on wireless networks and radio resource management, cs.NI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.IT and cs.SY.
